of
his
friend.
Elizabeth's
collected
behaviour,
however,
soon
quieted
his
emotion;
and
as
Miss
Bingley,
vexed
and
disappointed,
dared
not
approach
nearer
to
Wickham,
Georgiana
also
recovered
in
time,
though
not
enough
to
be
able
to
speak
any
more.
Her
brother,
whose
eye
she
feared
to
meet,
scarcely
recollected
her
interest
